2003年10月，有「Android之父」之稱的[[安迪·鲁賓|安迪·鲁賓]]<ref name="AndyRubin">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/04/technology/04google.html?_r=2&hp=&pagewanted=all |title=I, Robot: The Man Behind the Google Phone |accessdate=2008-10-14 |last=Markoff |first=John |date=2007-11-04 |publisher=The New York Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121109034230/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/04/technology/04google.html?_r=2&hp=&pagewanted=all |archive-date=2012-11-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[利奇·米纳尔|利奇·米纳尔]]<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news |url=http://www.boston.com/business/technology/articles/2007/09/02/introducing_the_google_phone/ |title=Introducing the Google Phone |first=Scott |last=Kirsner |accessdate=2008-10-24 |work=The Boston Globe |date=2007-09-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100104054533/http://www.boston.com/business/technology/articles/2007/09/02/introducing_the_google_phone/ |archivedate=2010-01-04 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>、{{tsl|en|Nick Sears|尼克·席爾斯}}<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.nokia.com/A4136002?newsid=918410 |title=T-Mobile Brings Unlimited Multiplayer Gaming to US Market with First Launch of Nokia N-Gage Game Deck |accessdate=2009-04-05 |date=2003-09-23 |publisher=Nokia |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090710001107/http://www.nokia.com/A4136002?newsid=918410 |archivedate=2009-07-10 }}</ref>、[[克里斯·懷特|克里斯·懷特]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/aug2005/tc20050817_0949_tc024.htm |accessdate=2009-04-23 |title=Google Buys Android for Its Mobile Arsenal |work=BusinessWeek |first=Ben |last=Elgin |date=2005-08-17 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5wk7sIvVb?url=http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/aug2005/tc20050817_0949_tc024.htm |archive-date=2011-02-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[美國|美國]][[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]][[帕羅奧圖_(加利福尼亞州)|帕羅奧圖]]共同成立了Android科技公司（英文：{{lang|en|Android Inc.}}），[[安迪·鲁賓|鲁賓]]把Android項目描述為「有極大的潛能以開發更智能的行動設備，以更了解其用户的位置及偏好<ref name="AndroidInc">{{cite web |url=http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/aug2005/tc20050817_0949_tc024.htm |title=Google Buys Android for Its Mobile Arsenal |first=Ben |last=Elgin |date=2005-08-17 |work=businessweek.com |publisher=Bloomberg L.P |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wk7sIvVb?url=http://www.businessweek.com/technology/content/aug2005/tc20050817_0949_tc024.htm |archivedate=2011-02-24 |accessdate=2011-02-24 |quote=In what could be a key move in its nascent wireless strategy, Google (GOOG) has quietly acquired startup Android Inc.... |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。」該公司早期的方向是為[[數碼相機|數碼相機]]開發先進的作業系統，此亦是2004年4月該公司向投資者介紹的基礎<ref name="pcworld-camera-os">{{cite web |first=Jay |last=Alabaster |title=Android founder: We aimed to make a camera OS |url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2034723/android-founder-we-aimed-to-make-a-camera-os.html |website=[[PC_World|PC World]] |publisher=[[International_Data_Group|International Data Group]] |date=2013-04-16 |accessdate=2017-05-09 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170510103305/http://www.pcworld.com/article/2034723/android-founder-we-aimed-to-make-a-camera-os.html |archivedate=2017-05-10 }}</ref>。儘管Android科技公司的創始人和員工過去都具有各自的科技成就，但是Android科技公司的經營只顯露出它在智慧型手機軟體的方面，該公司隨後認為相機市場不足以實現其目標，並且在5個月之後努力把Android轉移到一款可跟[[Symbian|Symbian]]及[[微軟|微軟]][[Windows_Mobile|Windows Mobile]]互相媲美的手機作業系統<ref name="pcworld-camera-os"/><ref>{{cite web |first=Chris |last=Welch |title=Before it took over smartphones, Android was originally destined for cameras |url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/4/16/4230468/android-originally-designed-for-cameras-before-smartphones |website=[[The_Verge|The Verge]] |publisher=[[Vox_Media|Vox Media]] |date=2013-04-16 |accessdate=2017-05-09 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170429062213/http://www.theverge.com/2013/4/16/4230468/android-originally-designed-for-cameras-before-smartphones |archivedate=2017-04-29 }}</ref>。

在Android科技公司成立初期，[[安迪·鲁賓|鲁賓]]在吸引投資者方面遇到困難，他也為公司花光所有錢，使公司面臨著被驅逐的景況。就在此時，[[安迪·鲁賓|鲁賓]]的一位密友，史蒂夫·帕爾曼（Steve Perlman）給他一個裡面裝有1萬[[美元|美元]]現金的信封，此後不久，此筆未披露的金額被視為種子資金。然而帕爾曼拒絕[[安迪·鲁賓|鲁賓]]所給他的股份，因他並非是以[[投資|投資]]的方式給[[安迪·鲁賓|鲁賓]]這筆錢，他表示：「我這樣做是因為我相信這件事，並且我想幫安迪。」<ref name="StevePerlman">{{cite news |url=http://www.airsla.org/broadcasts/BusinessWeek110802.mp3 |title=A Thousand Times Yes |accessdate=2011-11-09 |last=Vance |first=Ashlee |date=2011-08-07 |publisher=Bloomberg BusinessWeek |archive-date=2012-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120809084750/http://www.airsla.org/broadcasts/BusinessWeek110802.mp3 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Lisa |last=Eadicicco |title=THE RISE OF ANDROID: How a flailing startup became the world's biggest computing platform |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/how-android-was-created-2015-3 |website=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]] |publisher=[[阿克塞爾·斯普林格集團|Axel Springer SE]] |date=2015-03-27 |accessdate=2017-05-09 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170520025143/http://www.businessinsider.com/how-android-was-created-2015-3 |archivedate=2017-05-20 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Ashlee |last=Vance |title=Steve Perlman's Wireless Fix |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2011-07-27/steve-perlmans-wireless-fix |website=[[Bloomberg_Businessweek|Bloomberg Businessweek]] |publisher=[[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg L.P.]] |date=2011-07-29 |accessdate=2017-03-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170319032000/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2011-07-27/steve-perlmans-wireless-fix |archivedate=2017-03-19 }}</ref>

=== Android命名由來 ===
Android一詞最早出現於法國作家維利耶·德·利爾－阿達姆·利爾亞當（{{lang|fr|Auguste Villiers de l'Isle-Adam}}）在1886年發表的科幻小說《未來夏娃（{{lang|fr|''L'Ève future''}}）》中。他把外表像人的機器人取名為Android。

=== Android標誌 ===
{{Multiple image|image1=Android logo (2007-2014).svg|caption1=首个Android标志（2007–2014）|caption2=第二个Android标志（2014–2015）|caption3=第三个Android标志（2015–2019）|image2=Android Logo (2014-2015).svg|image3=Android logo (2014).svg|direction=vertical|width=250|align=left|image4=Android new logo 2019.svg|caption4=第四个Android标志（2019-现在）}}

Android是一個全身綠色的機器人，半圓形的頭部，有兩支天線和空白的點作為眼睛。它的頭部與身體之間有空白的區域，相似於一枚有平底的雞蛋，兩側各有兩個圓角矩形，作為它的雙臂。Android的標誌是由[[Ascender公司|Ascender公司]]設計，顏色採用了PMS 376C和RGB中十六進制的#A4C639來繪製，這是Android作業系統的品牌象徵<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.android.com/branding.html |work = Android |title = Brand Guidelines |date = 2009-03-23 |accessdate = 2009-10-30 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090831072954/http://www.android.com/branding.html |archive-date = 2009-08-31 |dead-url = yes }}</ref>。當中的文字使用了Ascender公司專門製作的稱之為“Google [[Droid|Droid]]”的字型<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.forbes.com/2008/09/25/font-android-g1-tech-wire-cx_ew_0926font.html |title = Android's Very Own Font |work = [[Forbes|Forbes]] |first = Elizabeth |last = Woyke |date = 2008-09-26 |archiveurl = https://archive.is/20120629171955/http://www.forbes.com/2008/09/25/font-android-g1-tech-wire-cx_ew_0926font.html |archivedate = 2012-06-29 |accessdate = 2011-12-20 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。有時候，它會以純文字的標誌展示<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.android.com/branding.html |work = Android |title = Android Brand Guidelines |date = 2009-03-23 |accessdate = 2010-04-10 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100207141607/http://www.android.com/branding.html |archive-date = 2010-02-07 |dead-url = yes }}</ref>。

=== Google的收購及發展 ===
2005年7月11日，[[Google|Google]]以高於$5,000萬美元的價錢收購了Android科技公司<ref name="Murky road despite dominance">{{cite web |first=Farhad |last=Manjoo |title=A Murky Road Ahead for Android, Despite Market Dominance |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/28/technology/personaltech/a-murky-road-ahead-for-android-despite-market-dominance.html |website=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=2015-05-27 |accessdate=2017-03-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706094446/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/28/technology/personaltech/a-murky-road-ahead-for-android-despite-market-dominance.html |archivedate=2017-07-06 }}</ref>，使其成為Google旗下的一部分。Android的關鍵人物包括[[安迪·鲁賓|安迪·鲁賓]]、利奇·米納爾和[[克里斯·懷特|克里斯·懷特]]，以及所有Android科技公司的員工都一併加入Google，作為收購的一部分。當時並沒有人知道Google為何會作出這項收購，引來許多的猜測，後來證實Google正是借助該次收購正式進入行動領域。根据前Google CEO[[埃里克·施密特|施密特]]的说法，收購Android目的是抗衡微軟，試圖阻止微軟在移動市場複製桌面市場的成功<ref name="first">[https://new.qq.com/omn/20180928/20180928A0RA63.html 谷歌十年前做Android只是为了杀死微软Windows Mobile] {{Wayback|url=https://new.qq.com/omn/20180928/20180928A0RA63.html |date=20181005195015 }}.騰訊網.</ref>。在Google，由鲁賓領導的團隊開發了一個基於[[Linux核心|Linux核心]]驅動的行動作業系統的平台，該開發項目便是Android作業系統。Google向[[代工生產|手機製造商]]及手機網絡供應商推出該平台，承諾提供一個靈活可靠並可升級的系統<ref>{{cite web |first=Ryan |last=Block |title=Google is working on a mobile OS, and it's due out shortly |url=https://www.engadget.com/2007/08/28/google-is-working-on-a-mobile-os-and-its-due-out-shortly/ |website=[[Engadget|Engadget]] |publisher=[[AOL|AOL]] |date=2007-08-28 |accessdate=2017-03-11 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312063351/https://www.engadget.com/2007/08/28/google-is-working-on-a-mobile-os-and-its-due-out-shortly/ |archivedate=2017-03-12 }}</ref>，為Android提供一個廣闊的市場。Google組織了一系列硬件及軟件的合作夥伴，並向運營商示意指公司開放到各種程度的合作<ref>{{cite web |first1=Amol |last1=Sharma |first2=Kevin J. |last2=Delaney |title=Google Pushes Tailored Phones To Win Lucrative Ad Market |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB118602176520985718 |website=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]] |publisher=[[Dow_Jones_&_Company|Dow Jones & Company]] |date=2007-08-02 |accessdate=2017-07-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729160919/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB118602176520985718 |archivedate=2017-07-29 }}</ref>。

2006年12月，《[[華爾街日報|華爾街日報]]》和[[英國廣播公司|英國廣播公司]]（BBC）報導了Google有機會進入流動領域的傳聞<ref>{{cite news |last=McKay |first=Martha |url=http://record-bergen.vlex.com/vid/iphone-phone-linksys-versatile-cordless-62885923 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130205165207/http://record-bergen.vlex.com/vid/iphone-phone-linksys-versatile-cordless-62885923 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-02-05 |title=Can iPhone become your phone?; Linksys introduces versatile line for cordless service |work=[[The_Record_(Bergen_County)|The Record (Bergen County)]] |page=L9 |date=2006-12-21 |accessdate=2012-02-21 |quote=And don't hold your breath, but the same cell phone-obsessed tech watchers say it won't be long before Google jumps headfirst into the phone biz. Phone, anyone? }}</ref>，Google有可能推廣行動領域下的各種Google服務，並且將推出一款名為Google電話的[[自有品牌|自有品牌]]智慧型手機。另有傳聞指出，按照Google的作風，將有可能呈現出新的智慧型手機製造商和運營商模式。傳聞指其早期[[原型|原型]]跟[[BlackBerry|BlackBerry]]手機非常相似，沒有觸控螢幕和物理[[QWERTY鍵盤|QWERTY鍵盤]]，但這其實也是針對微軟而做的，因為當時的[[Windows_Mobile|Windows Mobile]]手機有很多都是這樣的設計<ref name="first"/>。然而2007年[[蘋果公司|蘋果公司]]推出[[iPhone|iPhone]]，這令Android創始人[[安迪·魯賓|安迪·魯賓]]對原型機大為不滿<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sohu.com/a/257748630_100255965?spm=smmt.mt-it.fd-d.12.1538697600023WRl5Apr |title=“喬布斯宿敵”：安卓之父的苦情創業史 |access-date=2019-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006000523/https://www.sohu.com/a/257748630_100255965?spm=smmt.mt-it.fd-d.12.1538697600023WRl5Apr |archive-date=2018-10-06 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，意味著Android系統的設計「不得不回到草稿重新來過」<ref>{{cite web |first=Daniel |last=Ionescu |title=Original Android Prototype Revealed During Google, Oracle Trial |url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/254539/original_android_prototype_revealed_during_google_oracle_trial.html |website=[[PC_World|PC World]] |publisher=[[International_Data_Group|International Data Group]] |date=2012-04-26 |accessdate=2017-03-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211210905/http://www.pcworld.com/article/254539/original_android_prototype_revealed_during_google_oracle_trial.html |archivedate=2017-02-11 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Chris |last=Ziegler |title=This was the original 'Google Phone' presented in 2006 |url=https://www.theverge.com/2012/4/25/2974676/this-was-the-original-google-phone-presented-in-2006 |website=[[The_Verge|The Verge]] |publisher=[[Vox_Media|Vox Media]] |date=2012-04-25 |accessdate=2017-03-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325035619/http://www.theverge.com/2012/4/25/2974676/this-was-the-original-google-phone-presented-in-2006 |archivedate=2017-03-25 }}</ref>。Google後來修改了Android系統的規範文檔，指出「支援觸控螢幕」，雖然「產品的設計是以離散物理按鈕作為假設，因此觸控螢幕不能完全取代物理按鈕」<ref>{{cite web |first=Chris |last=Ziegler |title=Google in 2007: 'a touchscreen cannot completely replace physical buttons' |url=https://www.theverge.com/2012/4/25/2974843/google-in-2007-a-touchscreen-cannot-completely-replace-physical/in/2731667 |website=[[The_Verge|The Verge]] |publisher=[[Vox_Media|Vox Media]] |date=2012-04-25 |accessdate=2017-03-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623190711/https://www.theverge.com/2012/4/25/2974843/google-in-2007-a-touchscreen-cannot-completely-replace-physical/in/2731667 |archivedate=2017-06-23 }}</ref>。

2007年9月，Google提交了多項行動領域的[[專利|專利]]申請。但並沒有人知道，Google將會推出的是一款名為Android的智慧型手機作業系統。更多的猜測是，Google會推出一款像[[iPhone|iPhone]]一樣的自有品牌智慧型手機系列。<ref name="EngadgetMobileOS">{{cite web |url=http://www.engadget.com/2007/08/28/google-is-working-on-a-mobile-os-and-its-due-out-shortly/ |title=Google is working on a mobile OS, and it's due out shortly |accessdate=2007-11-06 |last=Block |first=Ryan |date=2007-08-28 |work=[[Engadget|Engadget]] |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Hotwc1Ye?url=http://www.engadget.com/2007/08/28/google-is-working-on-a-mobile-os-and-its-due-out-shortly/ |archive-date=2013-07-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="WSJ">{{cite news |url=http://online.wsj.com/article_email/SB118602176520985718-lMyQjAxMDE3ODA2MjAwMjIxWj.html |title=Google Pushes Tailored Phones To Win Lucrative Ad Market |accessdate=2007-11-06 |last1=Sharma |first1=Amol |first2=Kevin J. |last2=Delaney |date=2007-08-02 |work=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]] |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HotxWAnj?url=http://online.wsj.com/article_email/SB118602176520985718-lMyQjAxMDE3ODA2MjAwMjIxWj.html |archive-date=2013-07-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="DT">{{cite web |url=http://www.directtraffic.org/OnlineNews/Google_admits_to_mobile_phone_plan_18094880.html |title=Google admits to mobile phone plan |accessdate=2007-11-06 |date=2007-03-20 |work=directtraffic.org |publisher=Google News |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012234409/http://www.directtraffic.org/OnlineNews/Google_admits_to_mobile_phone_plan_18094880.html |archivedate=2007-10-12 }}</ref>

